==Description== <!--T:2-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal.svg|24px]] [[Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal|Sketcher ConstrainHorizontal]] tool constrains lines or pairs of points to be horizontal (parallel to the horizontal axis of the sketch).

<!--T:16-->
{{Version|1.0}}: In most cases it is advisable to use the combined [[Sketcher_ConstrainHorVer|Sketcher ConstrainHorVer]] tool instead.

==Usage== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:17-->
See also: [[Sketcher_Workbench#Drawing_aids|Drawing aids]].

===[[Sketcher_Workbench#Continue_modes|Continue mode]]=== <!--T:18-->

<!--T:5-->
# Make sure there is no selection.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* {{Version|1.0}}: If the {{MenuCommand|Unified tool for automatic horizontal/vertical constraints}} [[Sketcher_Preferences#General|preference]] is selected (default): press the down arrow to the right of the {{Button|[[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorVer.svg||x16px]][[Image:Toolbar_flyout_arrow.svg|x16px]]}} button and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal.svg|16px]] Horizontal Constraint}} option from the dropdown.
#* If this preference is not selected (and in {{VersionMinus|0.21}}): press the {{Button|[[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal|Horizontal Constraint]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Sketch → Constraints → [[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal.svg|16px]] Horizontal Constraint}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|H}}.
# The cursor changes to a cross with the tool icon.
# Do one of the following:
#* Select two points.
#* Select a single line.
# A constraint is added.
# Optionally keep creating constraints.
# To finish, right-click or press {{KEY|Esc}}, or start another geometry or constraint creation tool.

===Run-once mode=== <!--T:19-->

<!--T:20-->
# Do one of the following:
#* Select two or more points.
#* Select one or more lines. Points can be included in the selection, but will be ignored.
# Invoke the tool as explained above, or with one of the following additional options:
#* {{Version|1.0}}: Right-click in the [[3D_View|3D View]] and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal.svg|16px]] Horizontal Constraint}} option from the context menu.
#* Right-click in the {{MenuCommand|Elements}} section of the [[Sketcher_Dialog|Sketcher Dialog]] and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal.svg|16px]] Horizontal Constraint}} option from the context menu.
# Depending on the selection one or more constraints are added.

